According to the question,<br><br><img src="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l1fii3jf/31a01bcf-6cb4-4621-8c0b-8550fccd05d4/f2b393b0-b139-11ec-b8d6-85d90e85ca61/file-1l1fii3jg.png?format=png" data-orsrc="https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l1fii3jf/31a01bcf-6cb4-4621-8c0b-8550fccd05d4/f2b393b0-b139-11ec-b8d6-85d90e85ca61/file-1l1fii3jg.png" loading="lazy" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh" alt="WB JEE 2019 Physics - Electrostatics Question 33 English Explanation"><br>Force experienced by the charge $$-$$q due to charge Q<br><br>$$F =  - {{2kQq} \over {{r^2}}}\cos \theta $$ ... (i) [where, $$k = {1 \over {4\pi {\varepsilon _0}}}$$]<br><br>From diagram, $$\cos \theta  = {x \over r}$$<br><br>By substituting the value of cos$$\theta$$ in Eq. (i)<br><br>$$F =  - {{2kQq} \over {{r^2}}}\,.\,{x \over r}$$<br><br>or $$F =  - {{2kQx} \over {{r^3}}}$$<br><br>or $$F =  - {{2kQx} \over {{{({x^2} + {d^2})}^{3/2}}}}$$ $$ \because $$ $$\left[ \matrix{
  {r^2} = {x^2} + {d^2} \hfill \cr 
  r = \sqrt {{x^2} + {d^2}}  \hfill \cr}  \right]$$<br><br>For, x &lt; &lt; d, so x<sup>2</sup> can be neglected<br><br>$$F =  - {{2kQx} \over {{d^3}}}$$<br><br>So, the force developed by negative charge ($$-$$q) due to the system of the charges as shown in the figure is,<br><br>$$F = {{ - 4kQqx} \over {{d^3}}}$$<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow F \propto x$$<br><br>So, the forced developed by negative charge is directly proportional to the distance x.
